1:45:11.847 --> 1:45:13.766
He's scared if he does, those
guys will beat him up again.

1:45:13.766 --> 1:45:16.018
What? No, I'm not. I never said
that I was scared of them.

1:45:16.018 --> 1:45:17.770
- You don't, though.
- You got beat up?

1:45:17.770 --> 1:45:19.772
You always dismiss
what he does, what anyone does,

1:45:19.772 --> 1:45:23.651
that's playful or imaginative
as a pastime or a hobby.

1:45:23.651 --> 1:45:25.486
You already won, Mitz.

1:45:25.486 --> 1:45:27.446
I surrendered.
I'm not taking the bait.

1:45:27.446 --> 1:45:28.989
Can you guys please
just cut it out?

1:45:28.989 --> 1:45:30.866
- Oh, who's baiting who?
- You're embarrassing me.

1:45:30.866 --> 1:45:32.451
I said I'd take him for his
polio shot the first five times

1:45:32.451 --> 1:45:33.869
- you asked me, didn't I?
- Well, you say you will,

1:45:33.869 --> 1:45:36.121
but I guess you don't mean it,
so I ask again

1:45:36.121 --> 1:45:37.831
- and again and again.
- He's scared of shots.

1:45:37.831 --> 1:45:40.376
- He's scared of the doctor.

1:45:41.210 --> 1:45:44.630
I am taking the goddamn monkey
to the vet, okay?

1:45:44.630 --> 1:45:46.173
Probably needs a tranquilizer

1:45:46.173 --> 1:45:47.675
with all this yelling.

1:45:47.675 --> 1:45:50.094
Can you ask your dad
about borrowing the camera?

1:45:50.094 --> 1:45:51.512
He'll say yes.

1:45:51.512 --> 1:45:53.514
Thank you.

1:45:53.514 --> 1:45:56.183
I'm filming Ditch Day.

1:45:56.183 --> 1:45:57.977
I think it's a great idea.

1:46:23.711 --> 1:46:25.713
- Nice!

1:46:30.968 --> 1:46:32.845
- Go, go, go, go, go!

1:49:05.748 --> 1:49:08.625
- Don't be scared.

1:49:13.922 --> 1:49:17.468
Your mom misses Phoenix
too much.

1:49:17.468 --> 1:49:18.844
Tell them the truth.

1:49:18.844 --> 1:49:20.846
And I can't leave.

1:49:20.846 --> 1:49:22.806
This is where my work is.

1:49:22.806 --> 1:49:24.141
I have to...

1:49:24.141 --> 1:49:25.726
That's crazy.

1:49:25.726 --> 1:49:28.562
You... you can't ruin everything

1:49:28.562 --> 1:49:30.773
because you miss one place

1:49:30.773 --> 1:49:33.108
and you're stuck someplace else.

1:49:33.108 --> 1:49:35.736
I miss Bennie too much.

1:49:35.736 --> 1:49:37.279
So?

1:49:37.279 --> 1:49:39.031
We all miss him.

1:49:39.823 --> 1:49:42.326
This is a different kind
of missing.

1:49:42.326 --> 1:49:43.952
Because what?

1:49:44.745 --> 1:49:46.622
You love Bennie?

1:49:46.622 --> 1:49:48.207
- Don't you love Daddy?

1:49:48.207 --> 1:49:49.291
Sure she does.

1:49:49.291 --> 1:49:51.251
- Of course I love Dad.
- And I love Mom.

1:49:51.251 --> 1:49:53.587
Then why is this
all of a sudden happening?!

1:49:53.587 --> 1:49:55.422
Stay together.

1:49:55.422 --> 1:49:58.383
You love each other,
and you love us,

1:49:58.383 --> 1:49:59.927
and we don't want this.

1:49:59.927 --> 1:50:02.095
We don't want to have to move
back and forth

1:50:02.095 --> 1:50:03.639
and not live with both of you.

1:50:03.639 --> 1:50:05.432
We can't. Dad, we can't.

1:50:05.432 --> 1:50:06.934
You're always so mean to him!

1:50:06.934 --> 1:50:08.852
That's why
you're getting divorced!

1:50:08.852 --> 1:50:10.771
It's because of you!

1:50:10.771 --> 1:50:12.147
Don't blame your mom.

1:50:12.147 --> 1:50:14.191
This wasn't her idea.
It was mine.

1:50:14.191 --> 1:50:17.194
- Don't-don't say that.
- No, it wasn't.

1:50:17.194 --> 1:50:19.822
She just said it was because
of Bennie, so stop lying!

1:50:19.822 --> 1:50:22.074
Both of you, stop lying!

1:50:22.074 --> 1:50:24.201
I'm giving your mom a chance

1:50:24.201 --> 1:50:28.914
to go back to, uh,
Phoenix to live...

1:50:55.482 --> 1:50:57.317
I don't understand
how you can go back

1:50:57.317 --> 1:50:59.611
to your beach blanket movie
after that.

1:50:59.611 --> 1:51:01.989
We're different, I guess.

1:51:17.963 --> 1:51:20.257
Is she gonna marry Bennie?

1:51:21.049 --> 1:51:23.218
If she wants to, she will.

1:51:24.970 --> 1:51:27.347
God, she's the most selfish
person in the world.

1:51:27.347 --> 1:51:30.559
It must've been hard for her,
married to a...

1:51:30.559 --> 1:51:32.561
a genius.

1:51:32.561 --> 1:51:34.521
Dad worships Mom.

1:51:34.521 --> 1:51:36.023
Okay.

1:51:36.940 --> 1:51:40.944
But maybe it's hard
being worshipped by someone

1:51:40.944 --> 1:51:42.946
you know you'll never
be as good as

1:51:42.946 --> 1:51:45.157
or ever do anything as good as.

1:51:45.157 --> 1:51:46.450
She...

1:51:47.576 --> 1:51:49.953
She laughs at Bennie's jokes...

1:51:51.580 --> 1:51:54.666
...but Dad's always
been her best audience.

1:51:54.666 --> 1:51:56.710
Come on.

1:51:56.710 --> 1:51:58.587
She'll be fine.

1:51:58.587 --> 1:52:01.548
She'll tell herself everything
happens for a reason.

1:52:01.548 --> 1:52:03.884
She'll make excuses
like she always does.

1:52:03.884 --> 1:52:05.886
You're way more selfish
than her.

1:52:07.679 --> 1:52:09.723
That's why you're angry at her.

1:52:09.723 --> 1:52:12.684
It's because she's scared,

1:52:12.684 --> 1:52:14.895
just like you, Sammy.

1:52:15.896 --> 1:52:19.900
Out of everyone
in this out-of-control,

1:52:19.900 --> 1:52:23.236
falling-apart family,

1:52:23.236 --> 1:52:26.406
the one who's most like Mitzi
is you.

1:52:29.368 --> 1:52:30.744
Wait.

1:52:32.913 --> 1:52:34.831
Look, before I show this
to the whole school,

1:52:34.831 --> 1:52:37.292
could you please
watch it with me?

1:53:24.131 --> 1:53:26.842
- Hold your breath!

1:53:33.348 --> 1:53:35.017
Here.

1:53:35.017 --> 1:53:38.103
Oh, wow.

1:53:48.739 --> 1:53:51.116
Did you find Jesus?

1:53:52.534 --> 1:53:54.453
In a jewelry store.

1:54:26.276 --> 1:54:27.944
Hey, man, look who's here.

1:54:27.944 --> 1:54:29.613
Hey!
Let's get this party started!

1:54:29.613 --> 1:54:31.698
- Let the festivities begin.

1:54:33.533 --> 1:54:35.535
So, in September,
when I move to L.A.,

1:54:35.535 --> 1:54:38.205
I'm gonna try and get work
in a movie studio.

1:54:38.205 --> 1:54:40.415
Thought you were going
to college.

1:54:41.500 --> 1:54:43.293
Could you...

1:54:44.377 --> 1:54:46.296
Would you ever consider
coming with me?

1:54:46.296 --> 1:54:48.507
I'm going to Texas A&M.

1:54:48.507 --> 1:54:49.716
You know that.

1:54:49.716 --> 1:54:52.469
Yes, I do.

1:54:52.469 --> 1:54:55.097
But I thought...

1:54:56.807 --> 1:55:00.477
...maybe you should
change your mind, because...

1:55:03.480 --> 1:55:05.524
Because what?

1:55:06.942 --> 1:55:09.152
- Because I love you.
- Ow!

1:55:09.152 --> 1:55:10.612
- Sammy!
- Oh, sorry!

1:55:10.612 --> 1:55:13.031
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

1:55:13.824 --> 1:55:16.118
That's not possible.

1:55:16.118 --> 1:55:17.410
- What?

1:55:17.410 --> 1:55:18.829
N-No, it is.

1:55:18.829 --> 1:55:20.956
- Monica, I love you.

1:55:20.956 --> 1:55:23.041
That's impossible. Sammy...

1:55:23.041 --> 1:55:24.626
Sam.

1:55:25.710 --> 1:55:27.963
We only started dating like...

1:55:30.257 --> 1:55:31.842
Everything was so normal before.

1:55:31.842 --> 1:55:33.176
Why are you acting so...

1:55:33.176 --> 1:55:35.262
No, because
nothing's normal now.

1:55:35.262 --> 1:55:37.472
They're getting a divorce.

1:55:38.932 --> 1:55:40.600
What are you talking about?

1:55:40.600 --> 1:55:43.311
My mom and dad,
they're splitting up.

1:55:47.357 --> 1:55:49.943
Jesus Christ! This is prom!

1:55:49.943 --> 1:55:52.863
You can't just blurt something
out like that at prom!

1:55:52.863 --> 1:55:54.739
Wait.

1:55:56.950 --> 1:55:58.493
Monica!

1:55:58.493 --> 1:56:00.287
Look, that's-that's got
nothing to do with us, okay?

1:56:00.287 --> 1:56:02.205
- I'm not... -That's not why
I said that I love you.

1:56:02.205 --> 1:56:04.082
- I don't know why I...
- I'm not gonna change

1:56:04.082 --> 1:56:05.750
my whole life
and move to Hollywood

1:56:05.750 --> 1:56:09.462
because your parents are having
marital difficulties.

1:56:25.395 --> 1:56:27.814
You can get a refund.
I hardly wore it at all.

1:56:31.359 --> 1:56:33.612
Are you breaking up with me?

1:56:33.612 --> 1:56:38.533
Not at prom,
but of course, eventually.

1:56:41.286 --> 1:56:43.455
I'm gonna pray on it.

1:56:43.455 --> 1:56:47.375
And I'm gonna pray
really, really hard for you

1:56:47.375 --> 1:56:50.003
because you're such a fun boy
to kiss, but...

1:56:51.504 --> 1:56:53.173
Thank you. Thank you.

1:56:53.173 --> 1:56:55.675
Wonderful. Wonderful.

1:56:55.675 --> 1:56:59.262
Let's thank our band
for that great music.

1:56:59.262 --> 1:57:02.599
Sometimes we just can't
fix things, Sam...

1:57:03.892 --> 1:57:07.854
...and all we can do is suffer.

1:57:09.689 --> 1:57:12.400
Now we're gonna take
a little break from the dancing

1:57:12.400 --> 1:57:16.529
for a very special moment
for the class of 1964.

1:57:17.656 --> 1:57:21.701
Um, Mr. Samuel Fabelman,
where are you?

1:57:21.701 --> 1:57:23.203
Where is he?

1:57:24.037 --> 1:57:25.914
Okay.

1:57:25.914 --> 1:57:27.207
Bagelman!

1:57:27.207 --> 1:57:28.667
Bagelman!

1:57:28.667 --> 1:57:30.377
- Okay, everybody.

1:57:30.377 --> 1:57:32.212
- Face this way. Grab a chair.

1:57:32.212 --> 1:57:34.381
Let's all get close
to the screen.

1:57:35.548 --> 1:57:38.802
Right up front. Very good.

1:57:40.053 --> 1:57:43.765
Mr. Fabelman,
this is your big moment.

1:57:43.765 --> 1:57:49.646
We're ready to watch
your Technicolor masterpiece,

1:57:49.646 --> 1:57:53.066
"Ditch Day 1964."

1:57:57.153 --> 1:58:02.575
And as they say way down south
in Hollywoodland, "lights..."

1:58:02.575 --> 1:58:06.746
Uh, "lights, camera, action!"

1:59:57.565 --> 2:00:00.193
- Oh, no!

2:00:29.931 --> 2:00:31.558
- Aw.

2:01:41.044 --> 2:01:43.630
Whoo! Let's go! Come on!

2:01:44.589 --> 2:01:47.383
No, no, no, no, no.

2:01:49.052 --> 2:01:52.597
Logan, you were so incredible
up there.

2:01:52.597 --> 2:01:54.599
It was amazing.

2:02:27.382 --> 2:02:29.509
Why'd you do that?

2:02:31.761 --> 2:02:33.638
What?

2:02:33.638 --> 2:02:36.391
Why'd you make me
look like that?

2:02:38.685 --> 2:02:41.062
- In the film?
- Yes, in the film!

2:02:41.062 --> 2:02:43.398
Oh, shit! Shit.

2:02:44.440 --> 2:02:46.192
What's the matter with you?

2:02:46.192 --> 2:02:48.027
I've been a...
a total asshole to you.

2:02:48.027 --> 2:02:50.029
- I broke your nose, and then...
- You didn't break my nose.

2:02:50.029 --> 2:02:51.781
- Then you go and make me look
like-like that. -You almost--

2:02:51.781 --> 2:02:53.533
- You didn't break it.
- What's wrong with you?

2:02:53.533 --> 2:02:56.536
Logan, all I did was hold the
camera, and it saw what it saw.

2:02:56.536 --> 2:02:59.372
Oh, bullshit! Fabelman,
you made me look like...

2:02:59.372 --> 2:03:01.791
like this golden kind of thing.

2:03:01.791 --> 2:03:03.209
- Yeah? -And Claudia,
she just kissed me.

2:03:03.209 --> 2:03:05.003
- Mazel tov.
- In front of the whole school.

2:03:05.003 --> 2:03:06.713
- Okay, great. -I treat her
shittier than I treat you,

2:03:06.713 --> 2:03:08.631
- and now she wants to...
- You're welcome, man. Jesus...

2:03:08.631 --> 2:03:11.509
No, no. Don't...
Don't go. Don't go.

2:03:11.509 --> 2:03:14.554
I want to know why you did that.

2:03:14.554 --> 2:03:16.556
I don't know. I ought to have
my head examined.

2:03:16.556 --> 2:03:17.890
Am I supposed to feel bad now

2:03:17.890 --> 2:03:19.517
about all that shit
we did to you?

2:03:19.517 --> 2:03:20.810
Do you feel bad
about all that shit?

2:03:20.810 --> 2:03:22.312
That's none of
your goddamn business!

2:03:22.312 --> 2:03:24.230
-'Cause you should feel bad
about... -Oh, right!

2:03:24.230 --> 2:03:25.898
That's why you did it. You want
me to feel like crap about...

2:03:25.898 --> 2:03:28.693
I wanted you to be nice to me
for five minutes!

2:03:28.693 --> 2:03:30.987
Or I did it
to make my movie better.

2:03:30.987 --> 2:03:32.405
I don't know why.

2:03:32.405 --> 2:03:36.075
You are the biggest jerk
I've ever met in my entire life.

2:03:36.075 --> 2:03:39.579
I have a monkey at home
that's smarter than you!

2:03:39.579 --> 2:03:43.708
You dumb, anti-Semitic asshole!

2:03:43.708 --> 2:03:46.127
I made you look like
you could fly.

2:03:47.128 --> 2:03:48.838
But I can't fly.

2:03:48.838 --> 2:03:51.049
I can outrun any guy
in Santa Clara County,

2:03:51.049 --> 2:03:52.925
and I worked real hard
to do that.

2:03:52.925 --> 2:03:55.595
But you... you make me feel
like I'm some kind of failure

2:03:55.595 --> 2:03:57.805
or a phony or...
or like I'm supposed to be

2:03:57.805 --> 2:04:00.558
some guy I'm never gonna be,
not even in my dreams.

2:04:00.558 --> 2:04:02.018
You took that guy,
whoever he is,

2:04:02.018 --> 2:04:03.936
wherever you got him from,
and you put him up there

2:04:03.936 --> 2:04:06.064
on that screen
and told everyone...

2:04:06.064 --> 2:04:07.482
everyone that that's me.

2:04:07.482 --> 2:04:09.776
And that's not me.
That's... It's...

2:04:11.569 --> 2:04:15.114
Goddamn it. Goddamn it.

2:04:18.618 --> 2:04:20.662
Jesus, it wasn't supposed
to make you upset.

2:04:20.662 --> 2:04:22.705
I didn't mean to freak you out.
I didn't mean...

2:04:22.705 --> 2:04:25.500
Who cares what you meant?

2:04:26.626 --> 2:04:28.795
Fabelman!

2:04:30.213 --> 2:04:31.589
Oh, shit.

2:04:31.589 --> 2:04:32.715
You liar! You backstabbing liar!

2:04:32.715 --> 2:04:34.967
I'm gonna beat your...

2:04:46.813 --> 2:04:48.815
You totally bought it,
his whole snow job.

2:04:48.815 --> 2:04:51.109
You ate it up. You moron.

2:04:51.109 --> 2:04:53.778
Logan, you are so conceited
and dumb.

2:05:19.053 --> 2:05:21.764
Is something about to happen?

2:05:22.765 --> 2:05:24.684
You like living dangerously,
Fabelman.

2:05:24.684 --> 2:05:26.519
No, I don't.
I really, really don't.

2:05:26.519 --> 2:05:28.146
Yes, you do.

2:05:28.146 --> 2:05:32.066
But you tell anybody
about me getting, um...

2:05:32.066 --> 2:05:35.737
upset, that would be a mistake.

2:05:38.030 --> 2:05:39.532
Our secret.

2:05:39.532 --> 2:05:41.200
Okay?

2:05:41.200 --> 2:05:42.994
Definitely.

2:05:46.539 --> 2:05:48.875
Unless I make a movie about it.

2:05:50.001 --> 2:05:52.712
Which I'm never ever gonna do.

2:06:18.237 --> 2:06:20.156
You never...

2:06:21.324 --> 2:06:23.159
What's it like?

2:06:24.911 --> 2:06:28.247
It kind of shows you how
out of control everything is

2:06:28.247 --> 2:06:32.794
and how y-you're not
in charge of anything.

2:06:35.338 --> 2:06:37.548
A-And how it doesn't matter.

2:06:37.548 --> 2:06:39.258
I better not.

2:06:40.259 --> 2:06:43.137
In my head, everything's
already out of control.

2:06:45.598 --> 2:06:47.767
- You're full of shit.

2:06:47.767 --> 2:06:50.603
I got to split.
Claudia's waiting for me.

2:06:55.817 --> 2:06:59.445
Life's nothing like the movies,
Fabelman.

2:06:59.445 --> 2:07:00.780
Maybe not.

2:07:00.780 --> 2:07:03.366
But hey, in the end...

2:07:03.366 --> 2:07:05.618
you got the girl.

2:07:28.516 --> 2:07:31.394
Must have been some night.

2:07:33.938 --> 2:07:36.357
Did Monica like the corsage?

2:07:36.357 --> 2:07:39.735
- Yeah.
- Well, I told you she would.

2:07:47.660 --> 2:07:49.912
That time when I hit you...

2:07:49.912 --> 2:07:52.874
In-in Phoenix, when I...

2:07:52.874 --> 2:07:55.501
Oh, God. You remember.

2:07:56.961 --> 2:07:59.046
Not really.

2:07:59.046 --> 2:08:00.965
Oh, for the love of God,
it's not like

2:08:00.965 --> 2:08:03.426
I spent my whole life
hitting you.

2:08:03.426 --> 2:08:06.053
Once. I hit you once.

2:08:06.053 --> 2:08:07.680
It should've been memorable.

2:08:07.680 --> 2:08:09.181
Before the swimming test.

2:08:09.181 --> 2:08:11.183
Yes, before the swimming test!

2:08:11.183 --> 2:08:13.519
Yes. Well, I-I...

2:08:13.519 --> 2:08:16.898
I s-slapped you on your back...

2:08:18.024 --> 2:08:20.192
...as hard as I could.
I screwed up your tryouts,

2:08:20.192 --> 2:08:22.028
and you-you couldn't get
your merit badge,

2:08:22.028 --> 2:08:23.571
and then you couldn't make
Eagle Scout.

2:08:23.571 --> 2:08:25.114
- Ma, I made Eagle Scout.
- And I...

2:08:25.114 --> 2:08:27.158
- It wasn't a big deal.
- Well, I left a goddamn mark

2:08:27.158 --> 2:08:30.036
on your skin
in the sh-shape of my hand.

2:08:30.036 --> 2:08:32.371
And I need you to say
you forgive me for doing that.

2:08:32.371 --> 2:08:35.958
- Well, okay. I forgive you.
- Because... Because...

2:08:37.209 --> 2:08:39.211
- Because you're my kid.
- Mom, I forgive you.

2:08:39.211 --> 2:08:41.213
And-and-and my kids
mean more to me than...

2:08:41.213 --> 2:08:43.215
- Mom, I forgive you.
- ...anything else on the Earth.

2:08:43.215 --> 2:08:44.884
- I forgive you.
- Because...

2:08:44.884 --> 2:08:47.219
Please, please. Because how
am I ever gonna forgive myself?

2:08:47.219 --> 2:08:49.597
- I can't.
- Mom, I-I-I...

2:08:49.597 --> 2:08:51.057
I forgive you.

2:08:51.057 --> 2:08:53.017
The eggs are burning.

2:08:53.017 --> 2:08:55.645
Oh, God.

2:08:59.899 --> 2:09:02.944
I'm doing this thing.

2:09:03.903 --> 2:09:06.405
And I-I don't know
if it's the right thing,

2:09:06.405 --> 2:09:09.033
but it's a life-and-death
thing for me.

2:09:09.033 --> 2:09:11.494
And I'm sorry,
but everybody else

2:09:11.494 --> 2:09:13.829
is gonna have to hang on
for dear life.

2:09:13.829 --> 2:09:15.915
And somehow,

2:09:15.915 --> 2:09:19.502
we will survive this, all of us.

2:09:19.502 --> 2:09:22.588
Even your father,
who I adore with all my heart.

2:09:22.588 --> 2:09:26.759
He deserves so much better
than what I'm doing, but...

2:09:29.804 --> 2:09:32.598
...but Bennie needs me, dolly.

2:09:32.598 --> 2:09:34.767
And I need him.

2:09:34.767 --> 2:09:36.268
So much so that without him,

2:09:36.268 --> 2:09:38.145
I'm turning into someone
I don't know

2:09:38.145 --> 2:09:41.190
and none of you
will know me anymore.

2:09:41.190 --> 2:09:43.109
I'll just be that hateful person

2:09:43.109 --> 2:09:45.111
who did that terrible thing
to your back.

2:09:45.111 --> 2:09:49.281
And yes, this is the most
selfish thing I have ever done,

2:09:49.281 --> 2:09:53.119
but I've got to do this now
because, Sammy...

2:09:54.412 --> 2:09:57.456
...you do what your heart
says you have to,

2:09:57.456 --> 2:10:00.459
'cause you don't owe anyone
your life.

2:10:01.669 --> 2:10:03.629
Not even me.

2:10:09.802 --> 2:10:11.846
Oh... Are they ruined?

2:10:11.846 --> 2:10:14.807
I-I-I can make some more.

2:10:14.807 --> 2:10:16.517
Oh, no, no, no.

2:10:16.517 --> 2:10:18.227
I like 'em burnt.

2:10:22.148 --> 2:10:24.316
So, Monica dumped me.

2:10:24.316 --> 2:10:26.110
She did?

2:10:26.110 --> 2:10:28.821
Yeah, after I told her
about the divorce.

2:10:29.655 --> 2:10:31.240
Huh?

2:10:32.158 --> 2:10:34.785
Probably shouldn't have
asked her to marry me.

2:10:34.785 --> 2:10:36.912
- You did not.
- Oh, but...

2:10:36.912 --> 2:10:39.498
- Oh. You did?

2:10:40.541 --> 2:10:44.086
- In so many words.
-Poor girl.

2:11:05.441 --> 2:11:06.859
Dad?

2:11:10.613 --> 2:11:12.865
Hey, Dad, I'm home.

2:11:23.918 --> 2:11:25.836
Sammy?

2:11:31.550 --> 2:11:33.886
I think I'm having
a heart attack.

2:11:39.558 --> 2:11:41.727
- Come here.

2:11:50.236 --> 2:11:52.238
It's a panic attack.
Your mother gets them.

2:11:52.238 --> 2:11:54.782
- What did you do when she'd
get them? -I made her tea.

2:11:54.782 --> 2:11:56.325
Okay.

2:12:02.206 --> 2:12:05.084
Plus, you're exhausted.

2:12:05.084 --> 2:12:07.086
You don't sleep.

2:12:07.086 --> 2:12:08.921
I hear you walking around
all night

2:12:08.921 --> 2:12:10.381
or typing those letters,

2:12:10.381 --> 2:12:12.007
and the three hours' drive
to the college

2:12:12.007 --> 2:12:13.884
- every day and back, it's...
- Oh, no, no, no.

2:12:13.884 --> 2:12:15.427
I can't go back to that dorm.

2:12:15.427 --> 2:12:17.096
Maybe your roommate
settled down.

2:12:17.096 --> 2:12:18.639
He voted for Goldwater.

2:12:18.639 --> 2:12:20.641
I can't go back.

2:12:20.641 --> 2:12:22.017
Dad...

2:12:24.937 --> 2:12:27.106
I don't know...

2:12:27.106 --> 2:12:29.275
what to do anymore.

2:12:30.234 --> 2:12:32.194
I don't want to disappoint you,

2:12:32.194 --> 2:12:35.489
and I promised
that I'd stick it out,

2:12:35.489 --> 2:12:38.325
but two years is like forever,
and I hate school.

2:12:38.325 --> 2:12:40.578
- Like, a lot.

2:12:40.578 --> 2:12:45.374
And I want to get work
on a movie or a TV show,

2:12:45.374 --> 2:12:47.293
so I send out all those letters,

2:12:47.293 --> 2:12:49.295
but nobody ever writes back.

2:12:49.295 --> 2:12:51.797
And my life is just
going by so fast,

2:12:51.797 --> 2:12:54.008
but it's not getting anywhere.

2:12:56.385 --> 2:12:59.221
Concentrate on sipping.
It'll calm you down.

2:13:04.560 --> 2:13:06.812
Here. Uh...

2:13:09.356 --> 2:13:12.318
You can go through the mail
while I get the soup hot.

2:13:34.048 --> 2:13:36.383
It's from Mom.

2:13:37.426 --> 2:13:39.428
It's just a bunch
of goofy photos

2:13:39.428 --> 2:13:41.263
from some kind of block party.

2:14:27.685 --> 2:14:29.478
Dad?

2:14:31.730 --> 2:14:33.482
Dad, what's...

2:14:42.992 --> 2:14:45.077
Oh, Dad, I didn't mean to...

2:14:45.077 --> 2:14:47.621
If you hate school so much,
don't go.

2:14:48.747 --> 2:14:50.582
But... Dad, we need...

2:14:50.582 --> 2:14:52.293
I don't know.
I would like you to

2:14:52.293 --> 2:14:54.336
because this film thing...
I don't know.

2:14:54.336 --> 2:14:56.588
Maybe I should have
put my foot down about it

2:14:56.588 --> 2:14:59.258
years ago, but...

2:15:00.801 --> 2:15:04.221
I know you're gonna work
like the dickens

2:15:04.221 --> 2:15:05.931
on whatever you wind up doing

2:15:05.931 --> 2:15:09.101
because you're a chip
off the old block.

2:15:13.772 --> 2:15:17.359
We're never not going to know
each other, Sammy.

2:15:20.779 --> 2:15:23.324
How do you know that?

2:15:23.324 --> 2:15:25.159
You and Mom don't anymore.

2:15:25.159 --> 2:15:27.286
Yes, we do.

2:15:28.203 --> 2:15:30.372
We always will.

2:15:31.290 --> 2:15:33.751
I know it because...

2:15:35.544 --> 2:15:37.880
...we've gone too far
in our story

2:15:37.880 --> 2:15:41.133
to actually say "the end."

2:15:50.476 --> 2:15:52.895
Uh, you missed something
in the mail.

2:16:19.713 --> 2:16:21.548
Good news?

2:16:24.343 --> 2:16:26.678
They've ordered 32 half hours,

2:16:26.678 --> 2:16:30.182
Fridays at 8:30 p.m. on CBS,
starting September 17th.

2:16:30.182 --> 2:16:31.892
We already have six shows
in the can.

2:16:31.892 --> 2:16:34.311
It's like Stalag 17
or The Great Escape,

2:16:34.311 --> 2:16:36.021
- except it's funnier.
- Mm.

2:16:36.021 --> 2:16:37.439
And it's for television.

2:16:37.439 --> 2:16:38.857
- And it's funny.
- Yeah.

2:16:38.857 --> 2:16:40.734
Or at least I pray to God
that it's funny.

2:16:40.734 --> 2:16:42.528
Hogan's Heroes--
that's the title.

2:16:42.528 --> 2:16:43.987
What do you think?

2:16:43.987 --> 2:16:46.323
- Pretty catchy, right?
- Catchy. Yeah.

2:16:46.323 --> 2:16:48.033
And if all goes well,

2:16:48.033 --> 2:16:52.621
I might be able to offer you
something next season.

2:16:53.414 --> 2:16:56.458
Maybe assisting an assistant
to an assistant.

2:17:01.380 --> 2:17:03.298
You don't want to be
in TV anyway.

2:17:03.298 --> 2:17:06.510
Um, your letter said as much.

2:17:06.510 --> 2:17:08.804
By the way, I love this letter.

2:17:08.804 --> 2:17:10.764
- Oh.
- I used to write a whole bunch

2:17:10.764 --> 2:17:12.474
of these letters
when I was your age.

2:17:12.474 --> 2:17:15.018
You want to make movies.
Am I right?

2:17:15.018 --> 2:17:16.562
Well, yeah. Yes, I do.

2:17:16.562 --> 2:17:18.939
But look, I'm just happy
to start anywhere,

2:17:18.939 --> 2:17:20.732
- and-and that doesn't...

2:17:20.732 --> 2:17:22.568
You know who you need to meet?

2:17:22.568 --> 2:17:25.404
I mean, not for a job,
'cause he doesn't do that.

2:17:25.404 --> 2:17:27.406
How would you like to meet

2:17:27.406 --> 2:17:30.409
the greatest film director
who ever lived?

2:17:30.409 --> 2:17:32.870
And he's right across the hall.

2:17:34.913 --> 2:17:36.623
Come on.

2:17:41.420 --> 2:17:43.380
Wait here a minute.

2:17:52.473 --> 2:17:54.600
Um, this is Nona.

2:17:54.600 --> 2:17:56.393
Nona's gonna look after you.

2:17:56.393 --> 2:17:57.769
Um, he's not here. He's...

2:17:57.769 --> 2:17:59.188
- He's at lunch.
- Right.

2:17:59.188 --> 2:18:01.273
- You want to wait?
- Yeah, he'll wait.

2:18:01.273 --> 2:18:03.025
Sit.

2:18:04.109 --> 2:18:05.819
Good luck.

2:18:11.283 --> 2:18:12.993
Could be hours.

2:19:41.707 --> 2:19:44.710
All right, kid,
you got five minutes.

2:19:44.710 --> 2:19:46.920
Probably one. Stand up.

2:19:50.424 --> 2:19:52.426
Hey. L-Lose the tie.

2:19:52.426 --> 2:19:54.678
You'll stand a better chance.

2:21:04.247 --> 2:21:07.125
They tell me you want to be
a picture maker.

2:21:08.460 --> 2:21:10.629
Um, yes, sir, I do.

2:21:10.629 --> 2:21:12.464
Why?

2:21:12.464 --> 2:21:15.050
This business,
it'll rip you apart.

2:21:15.050 --> 2:21:17.594
W-Well...

2:21:18.970 --> 2:21:20.138
Mr. Ford, I...

2:21:20.138 --> 2:21:22.474
So, what do you know
about art, kid?

2:21:24.810 --> 2:21:26.478
I-I love your movies so much.

2:21:26.478 --> 2:21:28.480
No. Art.

2:21:28.480 --> 2:21:30.982
See that painting over there?

2:21:33.151 --> 2:21:35.153
Uh, yeah. I mean yes.

2:21:35.153 --> 2:21:36.655
Yes, I do see it.

2:21:36.655 --> 2:21:38.532
Walk over to it.

2:21:44.413 --> 2:21:47.374
Well, what's in it? Describe it.

2:21:47.374 --> 2:21:49.251
Oh, okay. Um...

2:21:49.251 --> 2:21:51.253
So, there are two guys,

2:21:51.253 --> 2:21:53.505
and they're on horseback,

2:21:53.505 --> 2:21:55.257
and they're looking
for something.

2:21:55.257 --> 2:21:56.508
So maybe they're scouting...

2:21:56.508 --> 2:21:58.635
No. No.

2:21:58.635 --> 2:22:00.637
Where's the horizon?

2:22:00.637 --> 2:22:02.848
The-the horizon?

2:22:02.848 --> 2:22:05.350
- Where is it?
- Yeah, it's at the bottom.

2:22:05.350 --> 2:22:07.018
That's right.

2:22:07.018 --> 2:22:09.688
Walk over to this painting.

2:22:15.694 --> 2:22:17.070
Well?

2:22:18.697 --> 2:22:20.782
Right, okay.
So, there are five cowboys.

2:22:20.782 --> 2:22:22.951
- You know, they could be
Indian... -No, no, no, no, no!

2:22:22.951 --> 2:22:24.745
Where's the goddamn horizon?

2:22:24.745 --> 2:22:26.538
Um, it's-it's there.

2:22:26.538 --> 2:22:28.457
- Where?
- At the top of the painting.

2:22:28.457 --> 2:22:30.292
All right, get over here.

2:22:32.502 --> 2:22:34.713
Now, remember this.

2:22:34.713 --> 2:22:37.090
When the horizon's
at the bottom,

2:22:37.090 --> 2:22:38.967
it's interesting.

2:22:38.967 --> 2:22:41.428
When the horizon's at the top,

2:22:41.428 --> 2:22:43.555
it's interesting.

2:22:43.555 --> 2:22:45.599
When the horizon's
in the middle,

2:22:45.599 --> 2:22:48.560
it's boring as shit.

2:22:48.560 --> 2:22:51.313
Now, good luck to you.

2:22:52.189 --> 2:22:54.816
And get the fuck out
of my office!

2:22:54.816 --> 2:22:56.777
Okay.

2:23:00.405 --> 2:23:02.073
Thank you.

2:23:03.074 --> 2:23:04.993
My pleasure.
